article.description: Jake Blumrick threw for 311 yards and three touchdowns as Stephen F. Austin took control in the second quarter for a 34-7 Southland Conference win over Lamar on Saturday night.
article.headline: Blumrick throws 3 TDs, leads SFA to 34-7 win over Lamar
article.linkText: Blumrick throws 3 TDs, leads SFA to 34-7 win over Lamar
article.story: BEAUMONT, Texas -- Jake Blumrick threw for 311 yards and three touchdowns as Stephen F. Austin took control in the second quarter for a 34-7 Southland Conference win over Lamar on Saturday night. Tamrick Pace hauled in seven passes for 145 yards and one touchdown and Terian Goree caught five for 73 yards and a score. Kijana Amous rushed 21 times for 111 yards and a touchdown. SFA (4-5, 4-3) racked up 571 total yards with 31 first downs while limiting Lamar (1-7, 0-6) to 225 yards and 10 first downs. Lamar's Kirkland Banks hit Andrew Allen on a 6-yard scoring strike to tie the game at 7-7 in the first quarter. The Lumberjacks then scored 27 unanswered points and coasted to the win. SFA got consecutive wins for the second time this year. They dropped Houston Baptist 27-10 last week. They will face Nicholls (6-2, 5-1) next Saturday. --- More AP college football: http://collegefootball.ap.org and http://www.twitter.com/AP-Top25
